quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  6,71,"SAY: \"Should we appeal to something that can neither benefit nor harm us, instead of to God? Shall we turn on our heels now that God has guided us, bewildered like someone whom the devils have enticed away on earth, while his companions are calling him to guidance: ´Come to us!´"
  6,72,"SAY: \"God´s guidance means [real] guidance. We have been ordered to commit ourselves peacefully to the Lord of the Universe"
  6,73,´Keep up prayer and heed Him!´ He is the One before Whom you will (all) be summoned
  6,74,"He is the One Who really created Heaven and Earth. Any day He says: ´Be!´; then it is! His speech [means] the Truth and He will hold control on the day when the Trumpet is sounded. Knowing the Unseen and Visible, He is wise, Informed"
  6,75,"Thus Abraham said to his father Azar: \"Do you accept idols as gods? I see you and your folk are in obvious error"
  6,76,Therefore We showed Abraham sovereignty over Heaven and Earth so he might feel reassured
  6,77,"When night descended on him, he saw a star. He said: \"Will this be my lord?\" So when it set, he said: \"I do not like setting things"
  6,78,"So then as he saw the moon rising, he said: \"Will this be my lord?\"; and when it set, he said: \"If my Lord did not guide me, I would be a member of the lost folk"
  6,79,"So when he saw the sun rising (again), he said: \"Will this be my lord? This is [even] greater.\" As it set, he said: \"My people, I am innocent of what you associate [with God]! I have turned my face enquiringly to Him Who originated Heaven and Earth. I am no associator"
  6,80,"His people argued with him. He said: \"Are you arguing with me concerning God, while He has guided me? I do not fear what you associate with Him, unless my Lord should wish for something else. My Lord comprises everything in knowledge. Will you not be reminded"
  6,81,"How should I fear what you associate [with Him] while you do not fear having associated something with God for which He has not sent you down any authority? Which of either group deserves more security, if you know anything"
  6,82,"Those who believe and do not cloak their faith in wrongdoing will feel more secure and will be [better] guided"